{% block content %}
    <h2>User Guide</h2>
    <p>RECAPSE is an XGBoost model for predicting cancer recurrence events based on insurance enrollment and claims data.</p>
    <p>The first step is to preprocess the data. This is a time-consuming step that generates two files needed for the prediction step.
    The first file is a metadata file containing consolidated patient level data. The second file is a file containing all of the
    features used as input into the XGBoost prediction.</p>
    <p>After the preprocessed data is generated, the two files can be fed through the model to generate predictions.</p>
    <p>For details on creating the input files and the features required in the input data, see:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="{{ url_for('static', filename='recapse_data_processing_guide.docx') }}">Data processing guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="{{ url_for('static', filename='recapse_input_columns_needed.xlsx') }}">Data dictionary</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>Preprocessing options</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Job Name - A string that will be put in the automatically generated task ID to help you identify the task</li>
        <li>Data Type - Medicaid only, Medicare only, or both</li>
        <li>Length of medicaid</li>
        <li>Data Type - Medicaid only, Medicare only, or both</li>
    </ul>

{% endblock %}
